The paper deals with author name disambiguation in bibliographic databases, which is a problem that falls under the scope of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of crowdsourced annotations and semi-supervised learning for building an automated disambiguation system is related to deep learning (cs.DL) and machine learning (cs.ML). The paper also mentions the use of blocking strategies and ethnicity-sensitive features, which are techniques commonly used in database systems (cs.DB) and social network analysis (cs.SI).
